because maybe I just haven't gained the social skills necessary yet. Perhaps due to my isolation and deprivation in an all-boys school, multiplexed with comorbid parental trauma led me to not *be able* to develop those skills in the first place. Isolation. So why cry out? 

I wish there was something I could do. The question is: how do you socialise yourself? You can't. It's like a crux, an impossible bind. You aren't socialised, so you don't know how to get yourself socialised, so you can't be socialised... But of course there's a way to be socialised. I guess it just takes time and many, many mistakes.

Like how over time I'm noticing my patterns, figuring out how to become normal. Realising that you can show energy for girls without it being seen as creepy. It's a balance: enough to show your openness, without the excess to signal your un-socialised nature. 

I see so many cute girls when I'm out, getting this painful feeling in my chest. "What can I do? Please, tell me, I want you, is there something I can do to make you want me? To make me seem interesting enough?" Sound familiar? What happened to little Kyle, she loved you to death, she never meant to neglect you... but she suffered from something else. I've been hell-bent on taking full responsibility my entire life because maybe when I was younger it meant that I would learn how to earn the love. You needed it, needed it unconditionally, but it never came. And there's nothing you can do to make it come now. You can never get your mother's love back, nor can you get a girl to love you. 

That sounds depressing. "There's nothing you can do to get a girl to love you"... "[It's her choice.]" So what do I do? Just sit around? I guess. 

